                                                  Autogenerating Fast Packet-Processing Code Using Program Synthesis

                                                                                                                                                    Application of Kekre's fast code book generation algorithm for face recognition

                                                                                                                                                      •

                                                                                                                                                      • 
               
                                                                                                                                                    • T. K. Sarode

                                                                                                                                                    ICWET '10: Proceedings of the International Conference and Workshop on Emerging Trends in TechnologyFebruary 2010, pp 26–30https://doi.org/10.1145/1741906.1741911
                                                                                                                                                    
            
                                                                                                                                                    
               		
               
                                                                                                                                                    In this paper we propose fast face recognition system based on the Kekre's Fast Code
                  book Generation (KFCG) method. This algorithm can be easily implemented and number

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    The recent upsurge of Apps, APIs and Cloud platforms, combined with the perpetual
                  need of shorter time to market, motivates the need for approaches for rapid software
                  engineering to compose applications quickly. In this paper, we propose a portal based

                  controllers, account for a significant portion of the chip area. It is therefore vital
                  for system energy efficiency that idle devices can enter a low-power state while ...

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          Improving application launch times with hybrid disks
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          • Yongsoo Joo, 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            •

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          CODES+ISSS '09: Proceedings of the 7th IEEE/ACM international conference on Hardware/software codesign
                     and system synthesisOctober 2009, pp 373–382https://doi.org/10.1145/1629435.1629486
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          
               		
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          Application launch times, which are important to users, are primarily bounded by disk
                  seek times. A solid-state disk has a negligible seek time, but large solid-state disks
                  are not cost-effective. A hybrid disk, consisting of a large disk drive and a ...

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  Mining performance regression inducing code changes in evolving software

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    •

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  Runtime-driven shared last-level cache management for task-parallel programs

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    Parametric Trace Expressions for Runtime Verification of Java-Like Programs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    • Davide Ancona, 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      • 
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    • Angelo Ferrando, 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      •

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      •

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      • 
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    FTFJP'17: Proceedings of the 19th Workshop on Formal Techniques for Java-like ProgramsJune 2017, Article No.: 10, pp 1–6https://doi.org/10.1145/3103111.3104037
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    
               		
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    Parametric trace expressions are a formalism expressly designed for parametric runtime
                  verification (RV) which has been introduced and successfully employed in the context
                  of runtime monitoring of multiagent systems.
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    Trace expressions are built on the ...

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      Accelerated test for applications with client application and server software

                     and CommunicationJanuary 2017, Article No.: 100, pp 1–6https://doi.org/10.1145/3022227.3022326
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      
               		
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      Application analyses is important for smartphone markets and application developers.
                  Dynamic analysis involving actual execution of application requires severely long
                  time. Reducing monitoring time is an important issue. In this paper, we focus on ...

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        Embedded Runtime for Reconfigurable Dataflow Graphs on Manycore Architectures

                     for Multicore Embedded Computing PlatformsJanuary 2018, pp 51–56https://doi.org/10.1145/3183767.3183780
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        
               		
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        Embedded manycore architectures offer energy-efficient super-computing capabilities

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          Quantifying WCET reduction of parallel applications by introducing slack time to limit
                     resource contention
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          • Sébastien Martinez, 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            • 
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          • Damien Hardy,

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          RTNS '17: Proceedings of the 25th International Conference on Real-Time Networks and SystemsOctober 2017, pp 188–197https://doi.org/10.1145/3139258.3139263
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          
               		
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          In parallel applications, concurrently running tasks cause contention when accessing
                  shared memory. In this paper, we experimentally evaluate how much the Worst-Case Execution Time (WCET) of a parallel application, already mapped and scheduled, can be ...

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            Multicore-aware hybrid code positioning to reduce worst-case execution time

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                The performance of parallel code significantly depends on the parallel task granularity (PTG).                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               A Novel Graph-Based Program Representation for Java Code Plagiarism Detection
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              • Hayden Cheers, 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                •

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                • 
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              ICSIM '20: Proceedings of the 3rd International Conference on Software Engineering and Information
                     ManagementJanuary 2020, pp 115–122https://doi.org/10.1145/3378936.3378960
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              
               		
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              Source code plagiarism is a long-standing issue in undergraduate computer science
                  education. Identifying instances of source code plagiarism is a difficult and time-consuming
                  task. To aid in its identification, many automated tools have been proposed to ...

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                PLDI '11: Proceedings of the 32nd ACM SIGPLAN Conference on Programming Language Design and
                     ImplementationJune 2011, pp 355–366https://doi.org/10.1145/1993498.1993540
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                
               		
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                When dealing with dynamic, untrusted content, such as on the Web, software behavior
                  must be sandboxed, typically through use of a language like JavaScript. However, even
                  for such specially-designed languages, it is difficult to ensure the safety of ...

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        Replayable Execution Optimized for Page Sharing for a Managed Runtime Environment
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        • Kai-Ting Amy Wang, 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          • 
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        • Rayson Ho, 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          • 
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        • Peng Wu
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          • 
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        EuroSys '19: Proceedings of the Fourteenth EuroSys Conference 2019March 2019, Article No.: 39, pp 1–16https://doi.org/10.1145/3302424.3303978
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        
               		
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        We present Replayable Execution, a system for improving the efficiency of Function-as-a-Service
                  (FaaS) frameworks. It takes advantage of standard kernel features to reduce memory
                  usage and accelerate cold startup speed without changes to the OS kernel, ...

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    Impact of stack overflow code snippets on software cohesion: a preliminary study
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    • Mashal Ahmad, 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      •

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    Developers frequently copy code snippets from publicly-available resources such as
                  Stack Overflow (SO). While this may lead to a 'quick fix' for a development problem,

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      Tracking code patterns over multiple software versions with Herodotos

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      An important element of understanding a software code base is to identify the repetitive
                  patterns of code it contains and how these evolve over time. Some patterns are useful
                  to the software, and may be modularized. Others are detrimental to the ...

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        Runtime enforcement of regular timed properties
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        • Srinivas Pinisetty, 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          • 
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        • Yliès Falcone,

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        SAC '14: Proceedings of the 29th Annual ACM Symposium on Applied ComputingMarch 2014, pp 1279–1286https://doi.org/10.1145/2554850.2554967
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        
               		
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        Runtime enforcement is a verification/validation technique aiming at correcting (possibly
                  incorrect) executions of a system of interest. In this paper, we consider enforcement
                  monitoring for systems with timed specifications (modeled as timed automata). ...

                  turn is key to faster and more frequent delivery of solutions to customers. Testing
                  at the unit level allows program components to be tested in complete isolation, ...

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            Improving aspect-oriented programming with dynamic code evolution in an enhanced Java
                     virtual machine
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            • Thomas Würthinger, 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              •

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            Dynamic aspect-oriented programming (AOP) is a powerful approach for integrating new
                  features into running applications without disrupting their execution. In Java, dynamic
                  AOP frameworks often use runtime weaving of previously loaded classes, which is ...

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                Task-parallel Runtime System Optimization Using Static Compiler Analysis
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                • Peter Thoman, 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  •

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                Achieving high performance in task-parallel runtime systems, especially with high
                  degrees of parallelism and fine-grained tasks, requires tuning a large variety of
                  behavioral parameters according to program characteristics. In the current state of
                  the ...

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  Improving SSE parallel code with grow and graft genetic programming
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  • William B. Langdon, 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    •

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  GECCO '17: Proceedings of the Genetic and Evolutionary Computation Conference CompanionJuly 2017, pp 1537–1538https://doi.org/10.1145/3067695.3082524
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  
               		
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  RNAfold predicts the secondary structure of RNA molecules from their base sequence.
                  We apply a mixture of manual and automated genetic improvements to its C source. GI
                  gives a 1.6% improvement to parallel SSE4.1 code. The automatic programming ...

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      Dynamically reconfiguring software microbenchmarks: reducing execution time without
                     sacrificing result quality
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      • Christoph Laaber,

Gall,

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      ESEC/FSE 2020: Proceedings of the 28th ACM Joint Meeting on European Software Engineering Conference
                     and Symposium on the Foundations of Software EngineeringNovember 2020, pp 989–1001https://doi.org/10.1145/3368089.3409683
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      
               		
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      Executing software microbenchmarks, a form of small-scale performance tests predominantly
                  used for libraries and frameworks, is a costly endeavor. Full benchmark suites take
                  up to multiple hours or days to execute, rendering frequent checks, e.g., as ...

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        Optimizing a parallel runtime system for multicore clusters: a case study
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        • Chao Mei, 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          •

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        TG '10: Proceedings of the 2010 TeraGrid ConferenceAugust 2010, Article No.: 12, pp 1–8https://doi.org/10.1145/1838574.1838586
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        
               		
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        Clusters of multicore nodes have become the most popular option for new HPC systems
                  due to their scalability and performance/cost ratio. The complexity of programming
                  multicore systems underscores the need for powerful and efficient runtime systems
                  that ...

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            Code coverage for any kind of test in any kind of transcompiled cross-platform applications
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            • Matthias Hirzel, 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              • 
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            • Herbert Klaeren
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              • 
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            INTUITEST 2016: Proceedings of the 2nd International Workshop on User Interface Test AutomationJuly 2016, pp 1–10https://doi.org/10.1145/2945404.2945405
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            
               		
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             Code coverage is a widely used measure to determine how thoroughly an application
                  is tested. There are many tools available for different languages. However, to the
                  best of our knowledge, most of them focus on unit testing and ignore end-to-end tests
                  ...

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  Genetic improvement of GPU code
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  • Jhe-Yu Liou, 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    • 
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  • Stephanie Forrest, 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    • 
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  • Carole-Jean Wu
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    • 
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  GI '19: Proceedings of the 6th International Workshop on Genetic ImprovementMay 2019, pp 20–27https://doi.org/10.1109/GI.2019.00014
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  
               		
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  As the programming stack and tool support for GPU have matured, GPUs have become accessible
                  to programmers who often lack domain-specific knowledge of the underlying architecture
                  and fail to fully leverage the GPU's computation power. This paper ...

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    Automatically documenting program changes
